cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.DC, cs.CC. 

The problem of minimum dimensional arrangement with fixed points is a problem in computational geometry, which suggests cs.CG as the most likely sub-category. The problem also involves optimization and approximation algorithms, which could place it in cs.DS (data structures) or cs.DM (discrete mathematics). The use of LP relaxations and integrality gaps suggests cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing) or cs.CC (computational complexity) as possible sub-categories as well.
